Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/publisher/Concept
Object: A SKOS Concept, for example: a library subject term.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/publisher/hasResearchService
Object: Relates a House to a research service. A research service may belong to one House or both, for example: the Parliamentary Office of Science and Technology, a bicameral office.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/publisher/ResearchService
Object: A group of researchers, for example: in the Library of the House of Commons, in the Library of the House of Lords or the Parliamentary Office of Science and Technology.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/publisher/ResearchSection
Object: A group of researchers within the Library of the House of Commons having a particular focus, for example: the Parliament and Constitution Centre.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/publisher/Group
Object: A group of people. Groups may contain other groups or be empty.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/publisher/hasResearchSection
Object: Relates a research service to a research section within that service.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/publisher/EditorialBoard
Object: A group overseeing a publisher, for example: the board of POST, made up of Members of Parliament, considering and approving areas of research.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/publisher/ThingHavingPublisher
Object: A published thing, which has a publisher.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/publisher/House
Object: A parliamentary House, for example: the House of Lords.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/publisher/Publisher
Object: An entity responsible for making a resource available.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/publisher/hasPublisher
Object: Relates a thing, which has a publisher, to the publisher of the thing.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/publisher/hasEditorialBoard
Object: Relates a publisher to its editorial board.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/publisher/Agent
Object: Agents include people and groups, including those outside the Parliamentary Service, participating in parliamentary procedure and contributing to the wider work of Parliament.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/publisher/
Object: A model describing the publishing of material by offices within Parliament, for example: the House of Commons Library.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/publisher/hasFocus
Object: Relates a publisher to one or more policy areas, policy areas being represented as SKOS concepts.
